text: Ginger Campbell @docartemis  joins #TWiV to discuss palliative care for #COVID19 patients, and how to approach the disease from a goals of care perspective https://t.co/4PVRIaWl7I #SARSCoV2 https://t.co/kqBZJKRgUV

@gruber your recent column on using one COVID vaccine dose is misinformed. The data are not there contrary to what you have read. Plus two doses are likely needed to deal with emerging variants. Stick with tech please.

The entire #TWiV team assembles to discuss resurgence of #COVID19 in Manaus, Brazil, discovery of #SARSCoV2 related viruses in bats in Southeast Asia, and increased Ct values after administration of mRNA vaccine https://t.co/Ps6DTT4c3f https://t.co/zFTzq5GxQL

In #COVID19 clinical update 50, CDC guidance on school opening, decreased viral load after vaccination, randomized clinical trial of vitamin D, study of zinc + vitamin C, anticoag therapy effect on mortality, multisystem inflammatory phase in kids https://t.co/8hOONX22bS https://t.co/xnMjpQdH7P

Paul Offit joins #TWiV to discuss all things vaccine, including how #COVID19 vaccine development was accelerated, whether vaccines are safe and efficacious, difference between EUA and licensed vaccine, sterilizing immunity, herd immunity, and much more https://t.co/thVOjPmQiu https://t.co/HEAUq6oJvE

Daniel Griffin on CDC guidelines on mask use, drop in US test frequency, resurgence of #COVID19 in Brazil, impact of Pfizer vaccine on viral load, EUA for bamlanivimab + etesevimab, preliminary results of Tocilizumab in hospitalized patients https://t.co/JOrMai8vQh #TWiV https://t.co/7DBF5aJ3Tj

In this #COVID19 clinical update Daniel Griffin reviews effect of spike changes on mAb neut, Sputnik V safety and efficacy, increased reactogenicity after vax in seropositive individuals, single dose vax in seropositive HCW, three anticoagulant RCT https://t.co/XW4uK0VT4H https://t.co/BqcaielpP4

On this episode #TWiV explains why hydroxychloroquine failed in humans despite showing antiviral effects in cells, and reviews the published data on the Pfizer/BioNTech mRNA #COVID19 vaccine https://t.co/rc3A75JKRP #SARSCoV2 https://t.co/rPSHRe3SpS
